1 of subsequent placement out of the foster care system and until the
2 eligible student's graduation from high school or the date the eligible
3 student is twenty-one years of age, whichever comes first.
4 (3) The Foster Child Scholarships Act shall not be construed to
5 grant any expanded or additional authority to the State of Nebraska to
6 control or influence the governance or policies of any eligible school
7 due to the fact that the eligible school admits and enrolls students who
8 receive HOPE Scholarships or as requiring any eligible school to admit or
9 to continue enrollment of any student receiving a HOPE Scholarship.
10 (4) The department shall annually notify educational decisionmakers
11 about the Foster Child Scholarship Act, in order to increase awareness
12 and eligibility of potential beneficiaries.
13 (5) The department may adopt and promulgate rules and regulations to
14 carry out the Foster Child Scholarships Act.
15 Sec. 4. On or before December 1, 2026, and on or before December 1
16 of each year thereafter, the department shall electronically submit a
17 report to the Governor and the Legislature that includes:
18 (1) The number of eligible students receiving a HOPE Scholarship in
19 the most recent fiscal year;
20 (2) The total amount of HOPE Scholarships awarded in the most recent
21 fiscal year; and
22 (3) Demographic information for eligible students receiving HOPE
23 Scholarships including, but not limited to: (a) Income level; (b) grade
24 level; (c) race and ethnicity; and (d) geographic location.
25 Sec. 5. It is the intent of the Legislature to appropriate two
26 hundred thousand dollars from the General Fund for fiscal years 2025-26
27 and 2026-27 to the department to carry out the Foster Child Scholarships
28 Act.
29 Sec. 6. Since an emergency exists, this act takes effect when
30 passed and approved according to law.
